Policy.acknowledgement_statement: This work was supported in part by a California Institute for Regenerative Medicine (CIRM) grant GC1R-06673 and NIH grants EY021237, HG008118, HL107442, DK105541 and DK112155. iPSC RNA-seq was performed at the UCSD IGM Genomics Center with support from NIH grant P30 CA023100.
Policy.ic_specific_access_term: There are three consent groups associated with the iPSCORE (Whole Genome Sequence) dataset: 1) General Research Use, Not for profit use (GRU-NPU) - Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations; 2) Disease-Specific [Cardiomyopathy], Not for profit use, Methods (DS-CMP-NPU-MDS) - Use of the data must be related to Cardiomyopathy. Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations. Use of the data includes methods development research (e.g., development of software or algorithms); and 3) Disease-Specific [Cardiomyopathy and Mitochondrial Disease], Not for profit use, Methods (DS-CMP-MD-NPU-MDS) - Use of the data must be related to Cardiomyopathy and Mitochondrial Disease. Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations. Use of the data includes methods development research (e.g., development of software or algorithms).

GSR_Access.gsr_mode_label: Unrestricted access (institution did not respond within six months)
